#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/rio/skills/marketing-and-growth/ad-creative/references/generative-tools.md
M|references|Reference for using AI image generators, video generators, and code-based video tools to produce ad visuals at scale.
M|references|| Need | Tool Category | Best Fit |
M|references||------|---------------|----------|
M|references|| Static ad images (banners, soc) | Image generation | Nano Banana Pro, Flux, Ideogram |
M|references|| Ad images with text overlays | Image generation (text-capable) | Ideogram, Nano Banana Pro |
M|references|| Short video ads (6-30 sec) | Video generation | Veo, Kling, Runway, Sora, Seedance |
M|references|| Video ads with voiceover | Video gen + voice | Veo/Sora (native), or Runway + ElevenLabs |
M|references|| Voiceover tracks for ads | Voice generation | ElevenLabs, OpenAI TTS, Cartesia |
M|references|| Multi-language ad versions | Voice generation | ElevenLabs, PlayHT |
M|references|| Brand voice cloning | Voice generation | ElevenLabs, Resemble AI |
M|references|| Product mockups and variations | Image generation + references | Flux (multi-image reference) |
M|references|| Templated video ads at scale | Code-based video | Remotion |
M|references|| Personalized video (name, data) | Code-based video | Remotion |
M|references|| Brand-consistent variations | Image gen + style refs | Flux, Ideogram, Nano Banana Pro |
M|references|Google DeepMind's image generation model, available through the Gemini API.
M|references|**Best for:** High-quality ad images, product visuals, text rendering
M|references|**API:** Gemini API (Google AI Studio, Vertex AI)
M|references|**Pricing:** ~$0.04/image (Gemini 2.5 Flash Image), ~$0.24/4K image (Nano Banana Pro)
M|references|**Strengths:**
M|references|- Strong text rendering in images (logos, headlines)
M|references|- Native image editing (modify existing images with prompts)
M|references|- Available through the same Gemini API used for text generation
M|references|- Supports both generation and editing in one model
M|references|**Ad creative use cases:**
M|references|- gen soc media ad images from text descriptions
M|references|- Create product mockup variations
M|references|- Edit existing ad images (swap backgrounds, change colors)
M|references|- gen images with headline text baked in
M|references|**API example:**
M|references|```bash
M|references|curl -X POST "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-2.5-flash-image:generateContent" \
M|references|-H "cnt-Type: application/json" \
M|references|-H "x-goog-api-key: $GEMINI_API_KEY" \
M|references|-d '{
M|references|"contents": [{"parts": [{"text": "Create a clean, modern soc media ad image for a project management tool. Show a laptop with a kanban board interface. Bright, professional, 16:9 ratio."}]}],
M|references|"generationConfig": {"responseModalities": ["TEXT", "IMAGE"]}
M|references|}'
M|references|```
M|references|**Docs:** [Gemini Image Generation](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/image-generation)
M|references|Open-weight image generation models with API access through Replicate and BFL's native API.
M|references|**Best for:** Photorealistic images, brand-consistent variations, multi-reference generation
M|references|**API:** Replicate, BFL API, fal.ai
M|references|**Pricing:** ~$0.01-0.06/image depending on model and resolution
M|references|**Model variants:**
M|references|| Model | Speed | Quality | Cost | Best For |
M|references||-------|-------|---------|------|----------|
M|references|| Flux 2 Pro | ~6 sec | Highest | $0.015/MP | Final prd assets |
M|references|| Flux 2 Flex | ~22 sec | High + editing | $0.06/MP | Iterative editing |
M|references|| Flux 2 Dev | ~2.5 sec | Good | $0.012/MP | Rapid prototyping |
M|references|| Flux 2 Klein | Fastest | Good | Lowest | High-volume batch generation |
M|references|**Strengths:**
M|references|- Multi-image reference (up to 8 images) for consistent identity across ads
M|references|- Product consistency — same product in different contexts
M|references|- Style transfer from reference images
M|references|- Open-weight Dev model for self-hosting
M|references|**Ad creative use cases:**
M|references|- gen 50+ ad variations with consistent product/person identity
M|references|- Create product-in-ctx images (your SaaS on different devices)
M|references|- Style-match to existing brand assets using reference images
M|references|- Rapid A/B test image variations
M|references|**Docs:** [Replicate Flux](https://replicate.com/black-forest-labs/flux-2-pro), [BFL API](https://docs.bfl.ml/)
M|references|Specialized in typography and text rendering within images.
M|references|**Best for:** Ad banners with text, branded graphics, soc ad images with headlines
M|references|**API:** Ideogram API, Runware
M|references|**Pricing:** ~$0.06/image (API), ~$0.009/image (subscription)
M|references|**Strengths:**
M|references|- Best-in-class text rendering (~90% accuracy vs ~30% for most tools)
M|references|- Style reference system (upload up to 3 reference images)
M|references|- 4.3 billion style presets for consistent brand aesthetics
M|references|- Strong at logos and branded typography
M|references|**Ad creative use cases:**
M|references|- gen ad banners with headline text directly in the image
M|references|- Create soc media graphics with branded text overlays
M|references|- Produce multiple design variations with consistent typography
M|references|- gen promotional materials without needing a designer for each iteration
M|references|**Docs:** [Ideogram API](https://developer.ideogram.ai/), [Ideogram](https://ideogram.ai/)
M|references|| Tool | Best For | API Status | Notes |
M|references||------|----------|------------|-------|
M|references|| **DALL-E 3** (OpenAI) | General image generation | Official API | Integrated with ChatGPT, good text rendering |
M|references|| **Midjourney** | Artistic, high-aesthetic images | No official public API | Discord-based; unofficial APIs exist but risk bans |
M|references|| **Stable Diffusion** | Self-hosted, customizable | Open source | Best for teams with GPU infrastructure |
