M|references|```
M|references|1. Write ad script (use ad-creative skill for copy)
M|references|2. gen voiceover with ElevenLabs/OpenAI TTS
M|references|3. gen or render video:
M|references|a. Silent video from Runway/Remotion → layer voice track
M|references|b. Or use Veo/Sora/Seedance with native audio (skip separate VO)
M|references|4. Combine with ffmpeg if layering separately:
M|references|ffmpeg -i video.mp4 -i voiceover.mp3 -c:v copy -c:a aac output.mp4
M|references|5. gen variations (different scripts, voices, or languages)
M|references|```
M|references|For templated, data-driven video ads at scale, Remotion is the best option. Unlike AI video generators that produce unique video from prompts, Remotion uses React code to render deterministic, brand-p
M|references|**Best for:** Templated ad variations, personalized video, brand-consistent prd
M|references|**Stack:** React + TypeScript
M|references|**Pricing:** Free for individuals/small teams; commercial license required for 4+ employees
M|references|**Docs:** [remotion.dev](https://www.remotion.dev/)
M|references|| AI Video Generators | Remotion |
M|references||---------------------|----------|
M|references|| Unique output each time | Deterministic, pixel-perfect |
M|references|| Prompt-based, less control | Full code control over every frame |
M|references|| Hard to match brand exactly | Exact brand colors, fonts, spacing |
M|references|| One-at-a-time generation | Batch render hundreds from data |
M|references|| No dynamic data insertion | Personalize with names, prices, stats |
M|references|**1. Dynamic product ads**
M|references|Feed a JSON array of products and render a unique video ad for each:
M|references|```tsx
M|references|// Simplified Remotion component for product ads
M|references|export const ProductAd: React.FC<{
M|references|productName: string;
M|references|price: string;
M|references|imageUrl: string;
M|references|tagline: string;
M|references|}> = ({productName, price, imageUrl, tagline}) => {
M|references|return (
M|references|<AbsoluteFill style={{backgroundColor: '#fff'}}>
M|references|<Img src={imageUrl} style={{width: 400, height: 400}} />
M|references|<h1>{productName}</h1>
M|references|<p>{tagline}</p>
M|references|<div className="price">{price}</div>
M|references|<div className="cta">Shop Now</div>
M|references|</AbsoluteFill>
M|references|);
M|references|};
M|references|```
M|references|**2. A/B test video variations**
M|references|Render the same template with different headlines, CTAs, or color schemes:
M|references|```tsx
M|references|const variations = [
M|references|{headline: "Save 50% Today", cta: "Get the Deal", theme: "urgent"},
M|references|{headline: "Join 10K+ Teams", cta: "Start Free", theme: "soc-proof"},
M|references|{headline: "Built for Speed", cta: "Try It Now", theme: "benefit"},
M|references|];
M|references|// Render all variations programmatically
M|references|```
M|references|**3. Personalized outreach videos**
M|references|gen videos addressing prospects by name for cold outreach or sales.
M|references|**4. soc ad batch prd**
M|references|Render the same cnt across different aspect ratios:
M|references|- 1:1 for feed
M|references|- 9:16 for Stories/Reels
M|references|- 16:9 for YouTube
M|references|```
M|references|1. Design template in React (or use AI to gen the component)
M|references|2. Define data schema (products, headlines, CTAs, images)
M|references|3. Feed data array into template
M|references|4. Batch render all variations
M|references|5. Upload to ad platform
M|references|```
M|references|```bash
M|references|npx create-video@latest
M|references|npx remotion render src/index.ts MyComposition out/video.mp4
M|references|npx remotion render src/index.ts MyComposition --props='{"data": [...]}'
M|references|```
M|references|```
M|references|Need video ads?
M|references|├── Templated, data-driven (same structure, different data)
M|references|│   └── Use Remotion
M|references|├── Unique creative from prompts (exploratory)
M|references|│   ├── Need dialogue/voiceover? → Sora 2, Veo 3.1, Kling 2.6, Seedance 2.0
M|references|│   ├── Need consistency across scenes? → Runway Gen-4
M|references|│   ├── Need vertical soc video? → Veo 3.1 (native 9:16)
M|references|│   ├── Need high volume at low cost? → Seedance 2.0
M|references|│   └── Need cinematic camera work? → Higgsfield, Kling
M|references|└── Both → Use AI gen for hero creative, Remotion for variations
